				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well I just dinged 10 last night in Artisan and declared myself as a Scholar.  I'm wanting to go the spellcrafting route (is that "Sage"?  can't recall at the moment).
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I've been making a living by crafting Apprentice III spells and selling them for between 5sp and 10sp (depending on time of day and market conditions).  I've been averaging about 1gp per "session" (which is leaving my merchant online over night).
<br />

<br />
Just thought we could share tips/tricks, etc.  I just scribed my level 10 book last night and was surprised to see there were no new spell additions?  But then I realized there are other books now, not just "Artisan" books.
<br />

<br />
Any advice for progressing up the spellcrafting chain?  I'm looking for something other than "make 50 of these".  So far I've managed to level to 10 by creating a broad variety of spells.  This has also had the effect of bringing in a good amount of cash, since I'm only rarely flooding the market with one type of spell.
<br />

<br />
I'm thinking about making an alt to focus on woodworking (to make my quills).  Does that sound like a reasonable idea?
<br />

<br />
Anyway, if anyone has any general advice on how to become a wealthy spellcrafter, spill it!  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />EQ1:  Mujahid Mukhtaar - Arch Lich, Solusek Ro (Retired)
<br />
EQ2:  Mujahid Mukhtaar - Summoner, Mistmoore
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v398/Mujahid/Sigs/sig3.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
