				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is a little late for your reply but the advice of a second character is probably the best one in the long run. Shared bank slots are the bomb.
<br />

<br />
As a bonus, when your second character gets craftsman level be sure and hook yourself up with pristine maple boxes.
<br />

<br />
Another excellent tip would be to either play with friends doing the other trade skills, join a guild that has other tradeskillers, or make friends with the folks in your wholesaler merchant area. You'll find that people will remember what you do and will help you out in exchange for something they need.
<br />

<br />
I've made stuff for people for no cost (they gave me the items to make it) when they helped me as well. As specialized as the trades get in this game I can forsee guilds recruiting people based on their tradeskill specialty in the late game. What good guild would be without a Scholor, Alchemist, Woodworker, Armorer, etc.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
